---
import MiFoto from "../../assets/img/MiFoto.png";
---

<!-- Contenedor principal -->
<div
  class="mx-auto mt-20 flex max-w-6xl flex-col items-center gap-8 px-6 lg:flex-row "
>
  <!-- Imagen -->
  <div
    class="border-primary h-64 w-64 overflow-hidden rounded-2xl shadow-lg md:h-96 md:w-96 drop-shadow-[4px_4px_0_#7836cf]"
  >
    <img
      src={MiFoto.src}
      alt="Foto de Lautaro"
      class="h-full w-full object-cover"
    />
  </div>

  <!-- Texto -->
  <div class="flex-1 text-center text-gray-300 lg:text-left" "justify ">
  <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white">
    My name is <span class="text-white text-shadow">Daniela</span>
  </h2>

    <p class="mt-4">
    I am a <span class="text-primary font-semibold">Computer Engineer</span>
    specializing in
    <span class="text-primary font-semibold">Technical Art</span> for video games,
    a discipline that bridges
    <span class="text-primary font-semibold">programming</span> and
    <span class="text-primary font-semibold">3D art</span>
    to create immersive interactive experiences.
  </p>

  <p class="mt-2">
    My role is to connect the
    <span class="text-primary font-semibold">artistic vision</span> with the
    <span class="text-primary font-semibold">technical implementation</span>,
    ensuring that every 3D model, animation, and gameplay system is optimized and
    efficiently integrated into the game engine. I work with
    <span class="text-primary font-semibold">Unity</span>,
    <span class="text-primary font-semibold">C#</span>,
    <span class="text-primary font-semibold">Blender</span>,
    <span class="text-primary font-semibold">Maya</span>,
    <span class="text-primary font-semibold">3ds Max</span>,
    <span class="text-primary font-semibold">ZBrush</span>,
    <span class="text-primary font-semibold">Marvelous Designer</span>, and
    <span class="text-primary font-semibold">Substance Painter</span>.
  </p>

  <p class="mt-2">
    I have developed
    <span class="text-primary font-semibold">3D environments</span>,
    <span class="text-primary font-semibold">characters</span>, and
    <span class="text-primary font-semibold">props</span>, while also implementing
    <span class="text-primary font-semibold">gameplay mechanics</span>,
    <span class="text-primary font-semibold">user interfaces (UI)</span>,
    <span class="text-primary font-semibold">animations</span>, and in-engine systems
    within <span class="text-primary font-semibold">Unity</span>.
  </p>

  <p class="mt-2">
    My background includes a
    <span class="text-primary font-semibold">Bachelor's Degree in Computer Engineering</span>
    from <span class="text-primary font-semibold">UNAM</span>, a
    <span class="text-primary font-semibold">Diploma in Game Development</span>, a
    <span class="text-primary font-semibold">Diploma in 3D Animation</span>, and the
    <span class="text-primary font-semibold">Generation Colombia Unity Bootcamp</span>.
    I enjoy solving technical challenges and continuously expanding my knowledge to
    contribute to innovative game development projects.
  </p>
</div>
</div>
